abstract: Somali military officials report African Union forces ousted Shabab militants from Bardhere, one of their last major strongholds; 24 militants and two Somali soldiers were killed in battle, part of campaign by multi-African nation army to rid Somalia of Al Qaeda-affiliated Islamic extremists.
lead_paragraph: Shabab militants withdrew from the town of Bardhere, an agricultural center about 225 miles west of the capital, Mogadishu, as African Union and local troops moved in.

headline.main: Troops Seize Somali City From Shabab Militants
headline.print_headline: Troops Seize Somali City From Militants
